(Corrects headline of story published March 14 to say Eike
Batista received the proposals.)  Brazilian billionaire Eike Batista
may increase the capital of his shipbuilder  OSX Brasil SA (OSXB3)  by $1
billion, the company said in a regulatory filing today.  Batista received proposals for two-year loans of as much as
1.8 billion reais from Itau BBA SA and  Banco Bradesco SA (BBDC4) ,
according to the filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
